14/06/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian police said on Friday (June 12th) they have dismantled a drug trafficking ring as a result of a month-long investigation.
Police arrested five suspects, three of them bus drivers on international routes.
They are suspected of being involved in transportation and distribution of hashish, heroin, amphetamines, LSD and piperazine from Amsterdam to Serbia.
(Tanjug, B92, UPI - 12/06/09)
